column1:
NOTE:
Plants with combustible-fueled steam-electric generators with a sum of 100 MW or more steam-electric nameplate capacity (including combined cycle steam-electric generators with duct firing) are required to report cooling information.  (These plants are designated as Steam Plant Type 1).  Additionally plants with nuclear fueled generators, combined cycle steam-electric generators without duct firing and solar thermal electric generators using a steam cycle with a sum of 100 MW or more steam-electric nameplate capacity are required to report cooling information. (These plants are designated as Steam Plant Type 3).  Some plants that are neither Steam Plant Type 1 or 3 have voluntarily reported cooling information; this voluntarily reported information is also displayed.
